    <abstract>In the sub-chapter “Fude no chikara to shinkō no netsu 筆の力と信仰の熱 [The Power of the Brush and the Heat of Faith]” in Chapter 7 “Hoppō no arashi: Sangoku, Shin, Nanboku-chō no jidai 北方の嵐──三國・晉、南北朝の時代── [The Storms in the North: The Eras of the Three Kingdoms, the Jin and the Northern and Southern Dynasties]”, pp. 96-101, Toriyama writes about the Sutra Stone Valley (JSY), while showing a foto (originally made by Sekino Tadashi 關野貞?), rubbings of the Diamond Sūtra and calligraphic works by Wang Xizhi 王羲之.</abstract>
